    Lok Sang is a 3D
    Artist whose work combines realism with sci-fi elements. He is a team player who
    can also work independently on projects. He has worked in teams where the work
    has been shown in Vivid Sydney, Sydney Film Festival and has won accolades from
    the Australian Effects and Animation Festival.</p><p>Lok Sang has masters degrees
    in telecommunications engineering and animation/visualisation from the University
    of Sydney and University of Technology, Sydney, as well as a graduate diploma
    and bachelor degrees in interactive multimedia, engineering, 3D animation and
    management. He has trained for a year as an FX artist using Houdini at the Animal
    Logic Academy, and is currently involved in an independent project working with
    Blender and Unity. Lok Sang is also highly skilled in computer programming.</p><p>He is currently working full-time as a Technical Assistant with Industrial Light and
    Magic. Lok Sang has appeared as a credit on the TV series, <em>Obi-Wan Kenobi</em>.</p>

